    "html": "<p>Regret is one of the heaviest things a person can carry — especially regret tangled up with identity, faith, and the body. If you&#39;re navigating transition regret and you want a space that honors your faith, please know: you are not alone, and you are not beyond grace.</p>\n<h2>Grief is allowed here</h2>\n<p>Transition regret often carries real grief — for time, for relationships, for a future you once pictured. In faith communities, grief can sometimes get rushed, as though hope requires us to skip past sorrow. It doesn&#39;t.</p>\n<p>In counseling, we make room for grief <em>and</em> hope to exist together. We don&#39;t force either one. Sometimes the most healing thing is simply to let the grief be witnessed without judgment.</p>\n<h2>Shame is not the same as repentance</h2>\n<p>One of the most freeing distinctions in faith-centered work is the difference between <strong>shame</strong> and healthy reflection. Shame says, <em>you are bad.</em> It isolates and condemns. That&#39;s not the voice of grace.</p>\n<p>Healthy reflection — and, for those who frame it this way, repentance — is oriented toward freedom and restoration, not self-punishment. Together we can explore forgiveness in a way that releases rather than crushes.</p>\n<h2>Identity beyond a single chapter</h2>\n<p>You are more than any one chapter of your story. Part of this work is rediscovering who you are now — your values, your relationships, your sense of self — with self-compassion instead of self-condemnation.</p>\n<p>For clients who want it, Scripture and prayer can be a source of steadiness in that process. They&#39;re offered at your invitation, never imposed, and woven together with evidence-based clinical care.</p>\n<h2>You set the pace</h2>\n<p>This is voluntary, client-led work. Faith is a resource I can offer, never a result I require. You decide what to explore and when.</p>\n<p>If you&#39;d like to talk it through, you can learn more about <a href=\"/detransition-support/faith-and-identity\">faith and identity after detransition</a> or <a href=\"/contact\">reach out</a> when you&#39;re ready.</p>\n"
